        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 24 at 9:31AM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 929 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southeast of Bosque Bonita, moving east at 30 mph. This storm
will track across remote areas of Hudspeth county, across the Rio
Grande near Bosque Bonita.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Indio Mountains Research Station, Green River, and Bosque Bonita.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
